latestPosts.caption:
Testing ALL the nudes so you don't have to - and I found THE ONE!
Okay, can we talk about how overwhelming nude lip shopping is? I literally have a pile of every nude shade imaginable sitting in front of me and I'm having Vietnam flashbacks just looking at them 😅
Where do you even START when there are 47 different "perfect nudes" staring back at you?
Here's my strategy: strip away your natural lip color first, then test systematically. No more guessing games!
First up - Acting Natural (yes, based on the lipstick). This one is giving me straight beige vibes and honestly... I'm not mad at it but I'm not in love either.
But THEN... I tried Maximal Matte and y'all - I was legitimately scared to put this on because sometimes "maximal" means "looks like I ate dirt."
BUT OH MY GOD. This is IT. This is the nude that's been hiding from us! I literally don't know what to do with myself because it's that perfect "your lips but better" shade that we've all been desperately searching for.
The moral of the story? Sometimes you have to kiss a lot of beige frogs to find your nude prince 👑
Stop buying random nudes and hoping for the best! Come join us in The Makeup Revival (free!) where I teach you how to narrow down your perfect nude based on YOUR undertones - no more drawer full of "almosts"! 💋
#nudelips #liptesting #lipstick #makeuptips #liptips #beautytips #makeupadvice #lipcolor #makeuptutorial #liptutorial #makeupbasics #beautyeducation #makeupconfidence #makeupskills #beautyguide #makeuprevival #beautycommunity #makeuphelp #beautyknowledge #makeuplessons #beautyinsider #makeupexpert #beautysecrets #lipgoals #makeupmastery #lipswatches #beautystruggle #makeupjourney #lipsticks

If you have deeper skin with hyperpigmentation on your lips, THIS is your game-changer!
Do your lips have that purpley-blue or darker pigmentation that makes finding the perfect nude impossible? Let me guess what happens:
You try a nude lip gloss → it goes ashy and terrible You try something with more color → suddenly it's way too bold You're stuck between "dead lips" and "too much" with NO middle ground
Sound familiar? This is SO common for deeper skin tones, and here's why regular nudes fail you:
They're not accounting for the natural pigmentation you're working with! When you put a standard nude over darker or purple-toned lips, it literally can't do its job.
Here's your solution: Look for nudes with ORANGE undertones (like the one I'm showing). That orange tone acts as a color corrector, neutralizing some of that pigmentation so you can actually achieve that natural-looking nude you've been searching for.
It's not about covering your natural lip color - it's about working WITH it to create balance. The orange undertones do the heavy lifting, giving you that even, natural nude that actually makes sense on your skin.
Stop settling for ashy nudes or going too bold when all you wanted was something natural! Your perfect nude exists - you just need to know what undertones to look for.
Ready to master color theory for YOUR skin tone? Join us in The Makeup Revival (free!) where I break down exactly which undertones work for different pigmentation levels! 💋
